00:37:00,018 --> 00:37:02,587
Timers ready? Yes. Ready.

474
00:37:02,588 --> 00:37:03,954
We're ready for skier number 89.

475
00:37:03,955 --> 00:37:05,356
Yes, we're ready.

476
00:37:05,357 --> 00:37:06,557
All right.

477
00:37:06,558 --> 00:37:07,925
10 seconds.

478
00:37:07,926 --> 00:37:08,960
10 seconds.

479
00:37:13,732 --> 00:37:19,771
Five, four, three two, one. Go.

480
00:38:07,486 --> 00:38:08,953
Clear the course.

481
00:38:08,954 --> 00:38:11,322
Will you clear the course,
please?

482
00:38:11,323 --> 00:38:13,458
Okay.
They're on their way right now.

483
00:38:13,459 --> 00:38:14,590
Yeah. They just left here.

484
00:38:22,468 --> 00:38:25,070
Clear the course...
Will you clear the course, please?

485
00:38:58,637 --> 00:39:00,938
Where does it hurt, Jill?

486
00:39:00,939 --> 00:39:02,573
I can't feel anything.

487
00:39:02,574 --> 00:39:04,775
Can you feel your toes at all?

488
00:39:04,776 --> 00:39:07,845
No. Jill, it's Dave.

489
00:39:07,846 --> 00:39:09,448
We'll take care of her.

490
00:39:10,749 --> 00:39:12,683
All right, Jill,
listen to me now.

491
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:15,386
Just take it easy. These people are
gonna take care of you. All right?

492
00:39:15,387 --> 00:39:18,556
I'm gonna go down to the bottom and
I'll see you in a little while. Okay?

493
00:39:18,557 --> 00:39:19,725
All right.

494
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:23,529
Don and Jack, take her arms.

495
00:39:24,896 --> 00:39:26,497
Sean, take her legs.

496
00:39:26,498 --> 00:39:28,165
Skeeter, you take her feet.
We'll straighten her out.

497
00:39:28,166 --> 00:39:30,001
Very carefully. Very slowly.

498
00:39:32,003 --> 00:39:33,404
It's okay, Jill.

499
00:39:33,405 --> 00:39:34,839
It's okay.
Just let us do the work.

500
00:39:34,840 --> 00:39:36,974
Hang on.

501
00:39:36,975 --> 00:39:39,076
Straighten her legs out a little
more, Skeeter. Buddy...

