00:44:10,048 --> 00:44:14,985
My head... What's in my head?

524
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:16,421
It's the traction.

525
00:44:20,258 --> 00:44:21,259
Jill...

526
00:44:30,168 --> 00:44:31,703
You're gonna be all right, Jill.

527
00:44:32,938 --> 00:44:33,938
Do you understand?

528
00:44:35,774 --> 00:44:37,108
Don't see me like this.

529
00:44:40,011 --> 00:44:41,345
Sleep, Jill.

530
00:44:41,346 --> 00:44:43,148
Just close your eyes and sleep.

531
00:44:44,850 --> 00:44:46,918
If I sleep I'll never wake up.

532
00:44:48,319 --> 00:44:49,754
You're gonna
come out of it, Jill.

533
00:44:51,823 --> 00:44:53,958
You got to.

534
00:44:53,959 --> 00:44:55,961
Help me stay...
Stay awake, Buddy.

535
00:44:57,328 --> 00:44:59,865
Help me stay awake.

536
00:45:07,472 --> 00:45:10,107
There's been a
fracture dislocation

537
00:45:10,108 --> 00:45:12,410
of the spinal column
at the level of C 5.

538
00:45:15,013 --> 00:45:18,990
In plain talk,
it means her neck's broken.

539
00:45:21,186 --> 00:45:22,921
The spinal cord's
completely severed.

540
00:45:28,093 --> 00:45:29,394
Will it heal?

541
00:45:30,428 --> 00:45:32,830
It'll fuse.

542
00:45:32,831 --> 00:45:34,310
But that's not the
same as healing.

543
00:45:38,036 --> 00:45:42,107
What is the...
The prognosis? Yes.

544
00:45:43,775 --> 00:45:45,777
At this point,

545
00:45:48,079 --> 00:45:49,479
it's a matter of guess work.

546
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:51,089
We'll have to wait
for her to tell us.

547
00:45:52,350 --> 00:45:54,919
In the meantime,
all we can do is...

548
00:45:55,420 --> 00:45:58,256
Wait and hope.

549
00:46:00,325 --> 00:46:01,492
Hope that she'll walk?

550
00:46:04,262 --> 00:46:05,296
That she'll live.

551
00:47:03,188 --> 00:47:05,023
One, two, three.

552
00:47:45,596 --> 00:47:47,464
Anybody up there?

553
00:47:47,465 --> 00:47:50,601
Hi, I'm your doctor.
Dr. Pittman.

554
00:47:53,071 --> 00:47:54,339
There's blood on your shoe.

555
00:47:55,974 --> 00:47:57,175
I'll be darned.

556
00:47:58,376 --> 00:47:59,677
It better not be mine.

557
00:48:02,547 --> 00:48:03,881
You wait out here, Jerry.

558
00:48:08,987 --> 00:48:10,087
Jill.

559
00:48:10,088 --> 00:48:11,089
Mom, come here.

560
00:48:14,960 --> 00:48:15,960
Jill.

561
00:48:16,394 --> 00:48:18,929
I can't see you.

562
00:48:18,930 --> 00:48:20,431
Can you turn her over? Just did.

563
00:48:33,411 --> 00:48:35,113
Don't you cry, Mom,

564
00:48:36,614 --> 00:48:38,415
you'll get tears in your ears.

565
00:48:38,416 --> 00:48:40,677
Don't you cry or you'll
splash them all over my face.

566
00:48:44,655 --> 00:48:46,023
Now look forward.

567
00:48:46,024 --> 00:48:47,592
No. Just with your eyes.

568
00:48:53,098 --> 00:48:54,099
Gives me a headache.

569
00:48:55,133 --> 00:48:56,234
I'm about done.

570
00:48:57,602 --> 00:48:59,170
And back again.

571
00:49:00,438 --> 00:49:01,572
Good.

572
00:49:05,743 --> 00:49:07,411
Nurse.

573
00:49:07,412 --> 00:49:08,579
Thank you.

574
00:49:15,053 --> 00:49:16,753
That bad?

575
00:49:16,754 --> 00:49:19,289
Why do you say that?

576
00:49:19,290 --> 00:49:21,159
Beware of smiling doctors.

577
00:49:26,731 --> 00:49:28,566
Do you want to hear about it?

578
00:49:29,200 --> 00:49:30,235
Sure.

579
00:49:33,138 --> 00:49:35,006
There seems to be
nothing left below there.

580
00:49:37,475 --> 00:49:39,977
No movement,
no feeling of any kind.

581
00:49:43,414 --> 00:49:46,316
If the break had been a
fraction lower,

582
00:49:46,317 --> 00:49:48,187
you would've retained
the use of your hands.

583
00:49:50,688 --> 00:49:53,323
But if it'd been
a fraction higher,

584
00:49:53,324 --> 00:49:55,585
you wouldn't be able to
breathe without an iron lung.

585
00:50:01,066 --> 00:50:02,133
How long?

586
00:50:03,201 --> 00:50:04,402
How long what?

587
00:50:05,536 --> 00:50:07,004
Before I'm well?

588
00:50:12,643 --> 00:50:14,112
Jill... Dr. Pittman...

589
00:50:16,647 --> 00:50:18,115
You don't understand.

590
00:50:18,116 --> 00:50:19,484
Neither do you.

591
00:50:21,152 --> 00:50:24,321
I have this problem, you see,

592
00:50:24,322 --> 00:50:26,757
when I want something, I get it.

593
00:50:28,126 --> 00:50:29,459
I understand that.

594
00:50:29,460 --> 00:50:30,795
No, you don't.

595
00:50:31,696 --> 00:50:33,331
I'm gonna walk out
of this place,

596
00:50:35,166 --> 00:50:37,068
and if you tell anybody
anything different

597
00:50:38,803 --> 00:50:40,771
I'm gonna make you
look damn silly.

598
00:50:49,847 --> 00:50:50,847
Hi.

599
00:50:55,586 --> 00:50:57,087
How're you feeling?

600
00:50:57,088 --> 00:50:58,355
Super.

601
00:50:58,356 --> 00:51:01,226
I, I'm on my way back home,

602
00:51:02,427 --> 00:51:05,195
so, I just thought I'd come by

603
00:51:05,196 --> 00:51:07,597
and tell you that if,
if you need anything, I mean,

604
00:51:07,598 --> 00:51:09,333
anything at all,

605
00:51:09,334 --> 00:51:11,635
just ask them to call me and,

606
00:51:11,636 --> 00:51:13,203
I'll see what I can do.

607
00:51:13,204 --> 00:51:17,441
I, I think,
they're very good people.

608
00:51:17,442 --> 00:51:18,529
They're doing a good Job.

609
00:51:19,477 --> 00:51:21,545
Yeah. Look at all this stuff.

610
00:51:21,546 --> 00:51:22,713
Yeah. I saw that.

611
00:51:25,650 --> 00:51:27,651
How's Andy taking the success?

612
00:51:27,652 --> 00:51:30,420
You know,
Andy's been there before.

613
00:51:30,421 --> 00:51:34,224
She's... She's won
a lot of races.

614
00:51:34,225 --> 00:51:36,126
She's a good skier.

615
00:51:36,127 --> 00:51:38,095
She's a great skier.
She's a great skier.

616
00:51:52,810 --> 00:51:54,479
You have just about
everybody up here?

617
00:51:56,447 --> 00:51:57,515
Dave?

618
00:51:58,549 --> 00:51:59,584
Dave?

619
00:52:01,419 --> 00:52:02,553
Dave.

620
00:52:13,398 --> 00:52:14,599
Everything's okay.

621
00:52:17,802 --> 00:52:20,471
Everything's okay.

622
00:52:26,511 --> 00:52:27,845
I'll see you soon.

623
00:52:30,715 --> 00:52:31,849
Goodbye.

624
00:52:39,790 --> 00:52:44,394
"How sorry I was I had to
leave before seeing you awake."

625
00:52:44,395 --> 00:52:49,267
"But I intend to make up for it with a
whole lifetime of watching you wake up"

626
00:52:49,867 --> 00:52:51,768
"and go to sleep"

627
00:52:51,769 --> 00:52:54,271
"in our very own bed."

628
00:52:54,272 --> 00:52:57,274
"You can't imagine
how excited I was"

629
00:52:57,275 --> 00:52:59,509
"when I read you're..."

630
00:52:59,510 --> 00:53:02,579
"When I read you were
going to ski again."

631
00:53:02,580 --> 00:53:06,450
"But I knew you wouldn't
settle for anything less."

632
00:53:06,451 --> 00:53:09,854
"And by the time I can scrape
together enough money to visit you,"

633
00:53:10,955 --> 00:53:12,890
"you are going to walk to me"

634
00:53:13,691 --> 00:53:15,959
"and into my arms"

635
00:53:15,960 --> 00:53:18,296
"and we are going
to walk away together."

636
00:53:19,564 --> 00:53:20,798
"Love, Buddy."

637
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:24,369
Isn't he wonderful?

638
00:53:24,735 --> 00:53:25,836
Yes.

639
00:53:26,837 --> 00:53:28,873
You're a very lucky girl.

640
00:53:31,676 --> 00:53:33,543
Is this where they
keep the gimps?

641
00:53:33,544 --> 00:53:34,811
A.J.!

642
00:53:34,812 --> 00:53:36,813
Mom! It's A.J.

643
00:53:36,814 --> 00:53:37,882
Audra Jo.

644
00:53:38,949 --> 00:53:41,418
In the flesh.

645
00:53:41,419 --> 00:53:43,953
Look at you, on crutches.

646
00:53:43,954 --> 00:53:45,455
Grotesque, right?

647
00:53:45,456 --> 00:53:47,757
No. Fantastic.

648
00:53:47,758 --> 00:53:49,726
Unbelievable.

649
00:53:49,727 --> 00:53:50,995
Come here. Touch me.

650
00:53:52,597 --> 00:53:53,830
How'd you get here?

651
00:53:53,831 --> 00:53:55,332
I hitchhiked.

652
00:53:55,333 --> 00:53:57,834
I did. I hitched a ride
with my therapist.

653
00:53:57,835 --> 00:53:59,836
His family lives up here.

654
00:53:59,837 --> 00:54:01,738
And he's cute, too.
So what do you think of that?

655
00:54:01,739 --> 00:54:03,908
I think that's great.

656
00:54:13,418 --> 00:54:14,518
Open up.

657
00:54:14,519 --> 00:54:15,553
No.

658
00:54:28,466 --> 00:54:31,936
Well, I gotta go.

659
00:54:35,306 --> 00:54:36,941
You ever want to see me again?

660
00:54:42,980 --> 00:54:45,720
You know what they say,
"If your best friends won't tell you..."

661
00:54:46,517 --> 00:54:48,418
What do you want me to do?

662
00:54:48,419 --> 00:54:49,619
Give up?

663
00:54:49,620 --> 00:54:50,655
Stop trying?

664
00:54:51,456 --> 00:54:52,689
For what?

665
00:54:52,690 --> 00:54:54,524
An acting award?

666
00:54:54,525 --> 00:54:55,859
To walk.

667
00:54:55,860 --> 00:54:57,394
What's so great about walking?

668
00:54:57,395 --> 00:54:59,763
For gosh sake,
a three year old can walk.

669
00:54:59,764 --> 00:55:01,030
Well, I can't.

670
00:55:01,031 --> 00:55:02,766
I can't even move.

671
00:55:02,767 --> 00:55:04,468
Well, then face it.

672
00:55:04,469 --> 00:55:06,903
Admit it, Jill.
Quit playing the heroine.

673
00:55:06,904 --> 00:55:10,440
As I remember,
you were pretty heroic yourself.

674
00:55:10,441 --> 00:55:12,576
Seems to me,
you did a lot of laughing.

675
00:55:12,577 --> 00:55:15,360
Yeah. Well, I didn't tell people
I was gonna climb Mount Everest.

676
00:55:15,913 --> 00:55:18,047
Take it from a veteran gimp.

677
00:55:18,048 --> 00:55:21,351
You got to see what you are
and say what you are,

678
00:55:21,352 --> 00:55:24,179
before you'll be willing to work
with what little you've got left.

679
00:55:25,122 --> 00:55:26,122
Audra Jo,

680
00:55:27,825 --> 00:55:29,960
what if I don't have
anything left at all?

681
00:55:31,729 --> 00:55:34,398
Then you'll learn to
paint with your teeth.

682
00:55:34,399 --> 00:55:36,600
What's happened to you?

683
00:55:36,601 --> 00:55:38,602
Same thing that'll
happen to you.

684
00:55:38,603 --> 00:55:40,103
There's only one thing
that kills cripples

685
00:55:40,104 --> 00:55:41,939
and that's taking
themselves too seriously.

686
00:55:43,708 --> 00:55:46,443
You've got arms, Audra Jo.

687
00:55:46,444 --> 00:55:49,546
Sure. Come to C.R.C.,
I'll show you somebody without a face.

688
00:55:49,547 --> 00:55:51,581
I'll show you a baby
living in an iron lung.

689
00:55:51,582 --> 00:55:52,882
Stop it.

690
00:55:52,883 --> 00:55:54,951
So quit moaning about
your Olympic medals

691
00:55:54,952 --> 00:55:57,721
and start thanking God
you still got your head.

692
00:55:57,722 --> 00:55:59,690
Anything else
you pick up is gravy.

693
00:56:08,966 --> 00:56:10,134
Audra Jo.

694
00:56:11,569 --> 00:56:12,569
What?

695
00:56:14,472 --> 00:56:17,040
They say I could have won.

696
00:56:17,041 --> 00:56:18,142
Did know that?

697
00:56:19,176 --> 00:56:20,478
Won what?

698
00:56:21,746 --> 00:56:23,013
The Snow Cup.

699
00:56:28,118 --> 00:56:30,554
The Snow Cup?

700
00:56:30,555 --> 00:56:32,957
Wasn't that the race
that ended your career?

701
00:56:42,933 --> 00:56:45,168
"An iron willed spirit"

702
00:56:45,169 --> 00:56:48,405
"declaring from a hospital bed
she's going to ski again."

703
00:56:50,007 --> 00:56:52,076
They say you're going
to ski again, honey girl.

704
00:56:52,910 --> 00:56:55,211
And you will.

705
00:56:55,212 --> 00:56:57,081
You will ski again.

706
00:57:03,688 --> 00:57:07,190
In the spring I was moved
to a hospital in Los Angeles

707
00:57:07,191 --> 00:57:09,926
and here, the job
of discovering what I had

708
00:57:09,927 --> 00:57:12,429
and what I didn't have,
began in earnest.

709
00:57:12,930 --> 00:57:15,098
That's it, Jill.

710
00:57:15,099 --> 00:57:17,634
Keep... Keep pulling
with your upper arm.

711
00:57:17,635 --> 00:57:19,703
Keep your head forward,
keep pulling

712
00:57:19,704 --> 00:57:21,404
forward with your upper arm.

713
00:57:21,405 --> 00:57:25,141
I began to become familiar with
words like extensors and flexors

714
00:57:25,142 --> 00:57:28,077
and deltoids and trapeziums.

715
00:57:28,078 --> 00:57:31,047
And I worked harder than
I've ever worked in my life.

716
00:57:31,048 --> 00:57:34,951
Keep going. That's it.
That's it, Jill. That's very good.

717
00:57:34,952 --> 00:57:36,186
Very good.

718
00:57:39,524 --> 00:57:41,858
Nice easy stretch now. Come on.

719
00:57:41,859 --> 00:57:43,861
Easy. There we go.

720
00:57:49,900 --> 00:57:51,868
Hi, I'm Dr. Enders.

721
00:57:51,869 --> 00:57:53,603
Hi, Doc.

722
00:57:53,604 --> 00:57:55,271
I can save you some time.

723
00:57:55,272 --> 00:57:57,507
I have biceps but no triceps,

724
00:57:57,508 --> 00:57:59,609
deltoids but no pecs,

725
00:57:59,610 --> 00:58:02,045
well, just a little bit
of pecs on the left side,

726
00:58:02,046 --> 00:58:03,279
but not much,

727
00:58:03,280 --> 00:58:05,214
I'll admit that's
a little unusual,

728
00:58:05,215 --> 00:58:06,916
but it's a transverse fracture,

729
00:58:06,917 --> 00:58:08,752
so the left side's
a little stronger.

730
00:58:08,753 --> 00:58:10,119
I see.

731
00:58:10,120 --> 00:58:11,187
How're you feeling?

732
00:58:11,188 --> 00:58:14,090
Just fine. How are you?

733
00:58:14,091 --> 00:58:16,192
I want you to straighten your
fingers out now. All right.

734
00:58:16,193 --> 00:58:18,261
I want to feel
pressure on my finger.

735
00:58:18,262 --> 00:58:19,741
Okay.
All right, go ahead and push.

736
00:58:20,698 --> 00:58:21,965
Push.

737
00:58:21,966 --> 00:58:23,633
Not your arm, Jill,
you're moving your arms.

738
00:58:23,634 --> 00:58:24,801
Okay.

739
00:58:24,802 --> 00:58:26,103
Okay, try again. Push.

740
00:58:27,271 --> 00:58:28,705
That's still your arm.

741
00:58:28,706 --> 00:58:30,640
Right.

742
00:58:30,641 --> 00:58:33,009
We'll try it one more...
One more time.

743
00:58:33,010 --> 00:58:34,010
Okay.

744
00:58:38,749 --> 00:58:39,749
Okay.

745
00:58:42,219 --> 00:58:44,220
Try not to look at your arm.

746
00:58:44,221 --> 00:58:46,569
Just concentrate on the pad
and we'll see what happens.

747
00:58:55,833 --> 00:58:56,867
There.

748
00:58:57,768 --> 00:58:59,603
That's it.

749
00:58:59,604 --> 00:59:01,705
Just concern yourself
with your shoulder.

750
00:59:01,706 --> 00:59:05,098
Let your shoulder do all the upward
movements and gravity do the downward ones.

751
00:59:09,046 --> 00:59:10,214
That's it.

752
00:59:12,116 --> 00:59:14,218
Come on. More with the shoulder.

753
00:59:15,119 --> 00:59:16,587
Aha, that's right.

754
00:59:21,692 --> 00:59:22,866
More of the shoulder. More.

755
00:59:27,598 --> 00:59:30,667
Push. You can do it.

756
00:59:30,668 --> 00:59:32,837
- Come on. Come on.
- Push, Jill. Push.

757
00:59:34,605 --> 00:59:36,139
Let's go.

758
00:59:36,140 --> 00:59:37,942
Come on. Come on.

759
00:59:42,012 --> 00:59:43,647
- Come on, Jill.
- Push.

760
00:59:43,648 --> 00:59:45,248
Come on, Jill.

761
00:59:45,249 --> 00:59:47,083
- Let's go.
- You can do it.

762
00:59:47,084 --> 00:59:48,318
Come on, do it.

763
00:59:56,393 --> 00:59:58,828
How's it look? You look fine.

764
00:59:58,829 --> 01:00:00,864
You look beautiful.

765
01:00:00,865 --> 01:00:02,165
Go over there and see how
it looks from a distance.

766
01:00:02,166 --> 01:00:04,300
Great. Just great.

767
01:00:04,301 --> 01:00:06,035
Where are the potato chips?
In your lap.

768
01:00:06,036 --> 01:00:07,271
No, go on.

769
01:00:25,089 --> 01:00:26,657
Hi.

770
01:00:29,359 --> 01:00:30,359
Come on in.

771
01:00:41,371 --> 01:00:42,807
You look beautiful.

772
01:00:44,208 --> 01:00:46,143
Do you think? Yes.

773
01:00:57,454 --> 01:00:59,423
Buddy, I missed you.

774
01:01:00,958 --> 01:01:02,259
I missed you.

775
01:01:04,294 --> 01:01:05,696
Could you kiss me?

776
01:01:19,777 --> 01:01:21,177
Are you all right?

777
01:01:21,178 --> 01:01:22,880
I'm wonderful.

778
01:01:25,382 --> 01:01:27,084
I tried to write every week.

779
01:01:27,451 --> 01:01:28,753
You did.

780
01:01:31,021 --> 01:01:32,456
Well, it's 'cause I tried.

781
01:01:40,798 --> 01:01:42,366
You want to see
something exciting?

782
01:01:43,801 --> 01:01:45,068
You want to show me?

783
01:01:45,069 --> 01:01:46,303
If you want to see.

784
01:01:48,038 --> 01:01:50,406
Well, that's what I came for.

785
01:01:50,407 --> 01:01:51,799
Well, go over there
and sit down.

786
01:01:52,743 --> 01:01:54,278
You don't need any help?

787
01:01:55,880 --> 01:01:57,847
You sure?

788
01:01:57,848 --> 01:01:59,448
Just go over there and watch.

789
01:01:59,449 --> 01:02:00,484
All right.

790
01:02:06,356 --> 01:02:07,958
Now, sit down.

791
01:02:15,132 --> 01:02:18,802
Come on. I'm waiting.

792
01:02:18,803 --> 01:02:20,470
Hold your breath
and don't say a word.

793
