We all loved him very much.

1283
01:37:46,128 --> 01:37:47,629
We'll miss him so much.

1284
01:38:17,926 --> 01:38:19,527
Anybody ever ask you?

1285
01:38:20,362 --> 01:38:21,595
What?

1286
01:38:21,596 --> 01:38:23,165
To get married?

1287
01:38:26,468 --> 01:38:28,937
If he asked you,
how come you didn't?

1288
01:38:32,474 --> 01:38:35,476
I think it's time we go home.

1289
01:38:35,477 --> 01:38:37,912
Come on, everybody. Let's go.

1290
01:38:45,487 --> 01:38:50,324
I try not to let it, but sometimes
it all plays back in my head.

1291
01:38:50,325 --> 01:38:53,060
And when it does,
I remember the words

1292
01:38:53,061 --> 01:38:55,497
that Dick Buek said to me
the last time I saw him.

1293
01:38:57,199 --> 01:39:00,567
"How lucky I am to
have known somebody

1294
01:39:00,568 --> 01:39:04,106
or something that saying
goodbye to is so damned awful."
